            "root_cause_hypothesis": "The vulnerability arises from allowing the addition of sub-columns to a parent column that has an OBJECT(IGNORED) column policy, which can lead to inconsistent or unintended schema states.",
            "fix_logic": "The patch introduces a check during the addColumn operation to detect if any new column being added is a sub-column of a parent column with an OBJECT(IGNORED) policy. If such a case is detected, it sets a subject flag to prevent or specially handle this scenario.",
            "dependent_apis": [
              "AddColumnRequest.references()",
              "ColumnIdent.isChildOf(ColumnIdent)",
              "ColumnPolicy.IGNORED",
              "OBJECT",
              "Reference.column()",
              "Reference.columnPolicy()",
              "for",
              "if"
            ],
            "patch_intent_summary": "Prevent adding sub-columns to parent columns with OBJECT(IGNORED) policy during table alteration to maintain schema integrity.",
